LifeData.Reason: I really don't remember much from this time; I can only say what I've been told. I was an only child at this time, very restless, couldn't stay still, and very inquisitive, eager to grab and touch everything that sparked my curiosity.

During this period, I started kindergarten, learned to read, and really enjoyed it—I would literally read even the dictionary, though I stopped due to teasing and comments from relatives. Something else I remember from this time is that my mother would read me a fable or story every night. Also, this is when my brother was born; initially, it was hard to adapt to sharing both my parents' attention and my space and things, but I gradually got used to it. I was still very active, played a lot with neighbors and cousins, and also got injured quite often. I don't know why this comes to mind, but I remember feeling embarrassed about the moles on my face; relatives liked to make jokes about them, the same relatives who teased me for reading.

In these years, I started elementary school and discovered I was really good at understanding and memorizing, which was very useful in school, being good at school from here on was considered my only and great virtue. During this time, I also started wearing glasses, which was chaotic; the first pair didn't last even a month. My sister was born during this period, and the process of sharing wasn't as drastic since I was already used to my brother. This is when I started to gain weight, began to play outside less often, and watched a lot of TV—cartoons and documentaries that I could only watch when I had the TV to myself. I also discovered music; I was given a Discman which became a great ally, spending hours listening to music, mainly three albums: one by José José, another by Napoleón, and the last by Hombres G. It was also during these years that we first had relatives staying at our house, which happened repeatedly over the years, and I felt I had no space for privacy.

During this time, I continued to prove that I was good at school, even participated in a mathematics contest representing my school, only reaching the state level. I also started playing soccer for two seasons; I joined to see if it would help me lose weight, but I didn't like it, never did, and ended up quitting. In these years, I also met Nancy, my first love and girlfriend, haha, I never heard from her again after we finished elementary school. I began to get hooked on video games during this time and stopped playing with neighbors due to issues we had. I also underwent surgery for a cyst on my wrist.

This period was complicated; school, which used to be really easy, now became challenging, although I eventually got the hang of it, it took time. Problems between my parents started at home, and arguments became constant. It was during this time that I began to feel embarrassed about my weight but did nothing about it. I focused more on video games and music, listening to all sorts really.

Another difficult period, school became even harder for me, I really struggled to keep up. My parents separated during this time as well. I started smoking in this period; I did it very little, 4 a week at most, and it was also when I started drinking. There was a month when I went overboard since it was every week, so they decided to put me in boxing to keep me away from that. At first, I wasn't so convinced; I grew up believing I had to be careful with my operated wrist, that it wasn't very strong, but to my surprise, it never caused problems, I enjoyed that part of boxing, it was a sport that I really liked. I wasn't the best but I was good, I had 3 fights at events, winning 2 of them, and I still keep my trophies. I was proud of how strong I could punch and got really into it, there were days when I would train up to 3 hours. Also, because of the sport, I lost weight, looking back at those photos, I think that was the time when I was the thinnest I've been since I was 6, but I still felt fat, I remember that. During this period, I also remember that was when I discovered Rap, which would be the genre I listened to exclusively for years, I was fascinated that it didn't talk about what popular songs always talked about, love or heartbreak, this genre was different and that caught me. During this time I had my second girlfriend, Monse, I was very much in love, but everything ended a month and a half later when I found out that she was seeing someone else at the same time as me, and I chose to end the relationship after confronting the facts.

I entered university, I never really thought I would get in, everyone in my family at most had finished high school, only one uncle had completed university, I saw it as something very complicated, I remember that summer I only thought about what I would do when I was rejected from university. But I got in, looking back, beginnings were always complicated for me, I also found it difficult when I started at university, I was in the evening shift and had to travel to Azcapotzalco, there were days when I would leave home at noon and get back at midnight. I spent a lot of time on transport, on average 3 hours a day, I looked for a way to make the most of that time, and that's how I took up reading again. I left boxing during this time, I tried to continue practicing it after entering university but it got complicated and I decided to focus only on school, I became one of the best in school again, semester after semester I received my achievement diploma but they meant nothing, I think I even lost them. I gradually felt more confident again about my intelligence, engineering was really my thing, I always loved mathematics, and seeing them at such complex levels and realizing that I found them much easier to understand than many of my classmates brought me a lot of satisfaction and I liked that they came to me so I could explain what they didn't understand. During this time, I also met my best friend, from previous friendships I can only say that they lasted as long as the segment we shared, whether it was high school, middle school, or elementary school, but I felt that with him it was different, we learned together and had several things in common.

Really, since adolescence to date, I have not been lucky with women, I have not known how to get to anything more than a friendship, always taking the role of their shoulder to cry on, always listening to their problems and trying to help them overcome them. It was like this that one night of drinks started the story of how I ended up being the other man for a university classmate, I was in that situation for six months until she preferred to be well in her long-term relationship that she already had. I finished university, but I still needed to do my service and internships, I entered a company in the last month of university where I did my internships, I liked what the company was about, it was in the area of development and research, something very much in line with what I thought would be my ideal job. I lasted a year there, after finishing my internships they hired me. But there was a design and manufacturing error in a project that led to most of us workers being fired. I no longer had the school that validated me as someone excellent, it was and still is difficult to continue considering myself excellent without that validation because most of my life or a large part of it I was valued for my grades and my intelligence, it was the only thing I felt I was good at. I tried to make changes in my life at that time, that's when I went to a nutritionist, everything was going well, I lost weight very quickly, but it didn't help me feel better about myself, and even worse when the weight loss began to slow down and became more difficult I also ended up leaving that. During this time I also diversified my musical tastes, and having money from work I started going to concerts, and I really liked that part.

After I was fired, I spoke with my best friend, he was starting out as a contractor with his brother, and offered me a job, I was working as an installation technician. Before joining them, I always considered myself very unskilled for jobs that required using my hands, but with them, I was able to practice that part, I also confronted the fear I thought I had of heights, it was really just a matter of practice. Although I wasn't exactly working as an engineer, that experience was very useful. I stayed with him for two years until earlier this year when they went several months without work. That's when I entered where I currently work as a supervisor. The job isn't bad but I don't like it because there isn't much to think about. That part bores and displeases me. To feel comfortable I really need to be drawing and thinking, otherwise, I get bored and find it tedious, although for the same reason I have been getting more involved with the technical part and maintenance, which also adds to my experience. I tried to continue going to concerts but the job was very demanding. I kept reading since I spent a lot of time in transport, in these years I could say that I have only lived to work, I feel like a machine. I also took the seminar to get my degree at the beginning of the year, I finished it, I just need to do the paperwork, but for some reason that I don't know, I haven't done it... I'm very indecisive.
